The paper deals with dynamic matching in a stochastic market, which is a topic that falls under game theory (cs.GT) and decision making (cs.DM). The use of asymptotic analysis and computation of tight bounds suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The study of matching technology and prioritization can be seen as a form of optimization (cs.SI). Finally, the mention of kidney exchange programs in the abstract suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of economics (cs.EC).
